{
  "texts": [
    "This in turn, provides crucial supervision signal during training that regularizes the variance of the collision model and enables safe yet non-conservative behavior.We validate our approach on real-world hardware, showing significant navigation gains over two baseline groups.",
    "The first, including the ROS stack and MonoNav [4], builds occupancy maps from noisy depth estimates, often causing unsafe or overly conservative behavior (Fig. 3).",
    "The second, NoMaD [5]-a diffusion-based end-to-end policy that directly regresses robot trajectory based on the input RGB image-lacks the precision needed for cluttered scenes.",
    "We also present additional statistical results validating the accuracy and statistical consistency of our learned collision model.",
    "In the following, we restrict our review to works that use only monocular camera for navigation and exclude those that rely on depth sensors or LiDARs."
  ]
}